  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Selected COVID-19-related outcomesAs of 5 May 2023, when the WHO declared an end to the COVID-19 pandemic as a public health emergency [110], a cumulative total of 7 million confirmed severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2 (SARS-CoV-2) infections and 78,000 COVID-19 deaths had been reported across the nine selected countries of the EMR.",
    "By the end of the pandemic, Bahrain had the highest percentage of COVID-19 cases out of the population (40.8%) followed by Lebanon (18.6%), then Jordan (16.9%).",
    "Yemen had the highest case fatality rate (CFR) at 18%, followed by Sudan (7.9%), then Syria (5.5%).",
    "In contrast, UAE and Bahrain registered the lowest CFRs, both at 0.2% (Fig. 3).UAE and Bahrain also conducted the highest number of tests per million population, while Syria conducted the fewest.",
    "As for the percentage of positive COVID-19 cases out of the total tests conducted, Yemen had the highest percentage (113%) followed by Syria (39.5%), Lebanon (25.8%) and Tunisia (23%)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Selected COVID-19-related outcomesAs of 5 May 2023, when the WHO declared an end to the COVID-19 pandemic as a public health emergency [110], a cumulative total of 7 million confirmed severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2 (SARS-CoV-2) infections and 78,000 COVID-19 deaths had been reported across the nine selected countries of the EMR."
